<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetCallback.Constructor" Title="Constructor method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetCallback">LogTargetCallback</PageRef> ->
    Constructor
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>LogTargetCallback</TypeRef> constructor creates a target that invokes the supplied callback for each received message.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Warning">
      <Paragraph>
        Supplying an empty callback can cause logging to fail when the target attempts to invoke it.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[LogTargetCallback(std::function<void(const std::string&, ILogger::Severity, const std::string&)> callback);]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="std::function" Name="callback">The callback to invoke with the message scope, severity, and text.</ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="See also">
    <PageRefList>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetCallback">LogTargetCallback</PageRefListEntry>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetCallback.Create">LogTargetCallback.Create</PageRefListEntry>
    </PageRefList>
  </Section>
</XMLDocContent>
